            <h2>Subject Analysis:</h2><br>
            <h4>Grade 6 - EVS/Science:</h4>
            <div class="audit-container">

                <p>ACADEMIC AUDIT: EVS/Science - GRADE 6</p>
                <p class="audit-separator"></p>
                <p>1. PERFORMANCE METRICS:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>School Average: 41.7%</li>
                    <li>National Average: 55.3%</li>
                    <li>Competitive Variance: -13.7%</li>
                </ul>
                <p>2. LEARNING INSIGHTS:</p>
                <p>FOCUSED IMPROVEMENT OPPORTUNITY: Current performance trends
                    indicate scope to strengthen alignment with national
                    benchmarks. Additional emphasis on application-level
                    understanding within the EVS/Science curriculum can further
                    support student progress and confidence.</p>
                <p>3. ACADEMIC GUIDANCE & SUGGESTED ACTIONS:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Conduct an 'Error Analysis' session with students to
                        identify common traps.</li>
                    <li>Re-align the teaching of EVS/Science to focus more on
                        'Why' and 'How' rather than 'What'.</li>
                </ul>
                <p>4. STRATEGIC SUPPORT PLAN (Next 90 Days)</p>
                <ol>
                    <li>GUIDED ERROR REVIEW: Facilitated review sessions can
                        help identify whether student errors are primarily
                        conceptual or calculation-based, enabling more targeted
                        instructional support.</li>
                    <li>FOUNDATIONAL SKILL REINFORCEMENT Short, focused practice
                        sessions (approximately 20 minutes daily or weekly) on
                        core fundamentals in EVS/Science can support steady
                        improvement and confidence building.</li>
                </ol>
                <p>5. Suggested ACADEMIC Action Plan:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>A focused review of EVS/Science sub-topics with
                        comparatively lower performance can help identify
                        specific learning needs.</li>
                    <li>A short-term, structured reinforcement phase
                        (approximately 4 weeks) on core fundamentals can support
                        students in building confidence and consistency.</li>
                </ul>
                <p>Generated by: Academic Analytics Department</p>
            </div>

