                    <h3>How to Interpret the Radar Chart</h3>
                    <p class="audit-separator"></p>
                    <p><strong>Strengths</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Indicators where the school's line is
                            <strong>outside</strong> the national line.</li>
                        <li>Consistently high points across multiple axes.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p><strong>Areas for Improvement</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Indicators where the school's line dips
                            <strong>inside</strong> the national average.</li>
                        <li>Sharp inward dips that show specific sub-skills
                            needing attention.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p><strong>Performance Pattern</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>A broad, balanced shape suggests <strong>uniform
                                competency development</strong>.</li>
                        <li>An uneven shape highlights <strong>specific
                                gaps</strong> that can guide instructional
                            planning.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p><strong>How to Use This Information</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Identify sub-skills that require <strong>targeted
                                teaching strategies</strong>.</li>
                        <li>Plan <strong>interventions</strong> for students who
                            need additional support.</li>
                        <li>Celebrate and reinforce <strong>areas of strong
                                performance</strong>.</li>
                    </ul>
