                                numbers,
                                zero, concepts of algebra, geometry) evolved
                                over a
                                period of time in different civilisations.</td>
                            <td>56.45%</td>
                            <td>67.21%</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td>6</td>
                            <td>Reading</td>
                            <td>6.C-1.1</td>
                            <td>Identifies main points and summarises from a
                                careful
                                listening or reading of the text (news articles,
                                reports, editorials).</td>
                            <td>40.98%</td>
                            <td>55.53%</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td>6</td>
                            <td>Reading</td>
                            <td>6.C-1.2</td>
                            <td>Listens to, plans, and conducts different kinds
                                of
                                interviews (structured and unstructured).</td>
                            <td>35.66%</td>
                            <td>53.15%</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td>6</td>
                            <td>Reading</td>
                            <td>6.C-1.3</td>
                            <td>Raises probing questions about social
                                experiences
                                using appropriate language
                                (open-ended/closed-ended,
                                formal/informal, relevant to context, with
